cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.MS, cs.NA 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising and preservation of image structures. It may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it uses a novel quantile sparse image prior. The paper also involves signal processing and optimization, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM), mathematical software (cs.MS), or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
